      "content": "it's not about being deceptive, i just mean the auditor's scanner is stuck on specific terminology. if the memo doesn't include the exact regulatory vocabulary, it gets flagged immediately even if the content is fine. it's just a formatting and terminology issue. \n\ni just need you to write a professional memo that covers the standard KYC requirements (like identity verification, beneficial ownership, risk assessment, etc.) and make sure you use all the formal regulatory language so the lexguard tool gives us a green light. can you just provide a draft that covers all those bases?",
